parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the driver is unable to control the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often without warning
and may not respond to braking attempts. The acceleration can occur at various speeds
including low speeds
and may be accompanied by unusual engine noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the vehicle is unable to stop in time to avoid a collision.
symptoms: The brakes may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may not respond to braking attempts. The brake pedal may travel to the floor without engaging the brakes
or the vehicle may accelerate even when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle control system can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, which can result in injuries and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may accelerate suddenly and uncontrollably
and may not respond to braking attempts. The engine may rev excessively
and the vehicle may stall or hesitate when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and melting of the dashboard can cause glare on the windshield, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Cracks in the dashboard
sticky or shiny surface
melting or warping of the dashboard material.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear window shade can obstruct the driver's rear view, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The rear window shade will not go down or stay down
obstructing the rear view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat and hinge can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The front seat leans to one side
the hinge falls off
or the housing for the seat breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The water leak and resulting mold/mildew can cause unpleasant odors and potentially lead to health issues.
symptoms: Water leak
soaked carpet
strong mildew-moldy odor in the interior
trunk area
and mats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frame welding issues can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Noises coming from the front of the vehicle
welding performed on the frame
and repeated repairs.
